      "author": "lc0rp",
      "description": "## KeepSidian v2.0.4\r\n\r\n### Highlights\r\n- Added secure secret handling for sensitive credentials:\r\n  - Google Keep sync token\r\n  - Google Drive access/refresh tokens (when present)\r\n- Added automatic migration from legacy plaintext token settings to Obsidian secret storage (when available).\r\n- Kept backward compatibility for environments where secret storage is unavailable.\r\n\r\n### Improvements\r\n- Improved sync robustness by handling non-string vault adapter reads safely in note merge/overwrite paths.\r\n- Updated settings copy to clarify secure token storage behavior.\r\n\r\n### Quality\r\n- Added regression tests for secret-storage migration and persistence behavior.\r\n- Full local gate passed before release:\r\n  - lint\r\n  - tests\r\n  - build\r\n\r\n### Migration notes\r\n- Existing users keep working with no manual action.\r\n- Legacy plaintext token values are migrated to secret storage when supported by the user's Obsidian runtime.\r\n",
