      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What's Changed\r\n\r\n### Most Notable\r\n\r\n**Two-Way Sync is Here!**\r\n\r\nVersion 1.1.2 introduces the much-anticipated ability to push your Obsidian notes back to Google Keep! This release transforms KeepSidian from a one-way import tool into a true bidirectional sync solution.\r\n\r\n### Features\r\n\r\n**Two-Way Sync Functionality**\r\n- Upload notes from Obsidian back to Google Keep\r\n- Automatic two-way sync command that downloads first, then uploads\r\n- Smart conflict detection and resolution\r\n- Incremental sync based on last successful sync timestamp\r\n- Beta safeguards to protect your data during the rollout\r\n\r\n**Improved Token Retrieval Wizard**\r\n- New guided token retrieval flow with embedded webview\r\n- Improved error handling and user feedback\r\n\r\n**Faster Sync UX**\r\n- Batched logging for better performance\r\n\r\n### Fixes\r\n\r\n- **Frontmatter Repair**: Automatically fixes hyphenated frontmatter keys before sync\r\n- **URL Hardening**: More robust handling of Google Keep URLs\r\n- **Duplicate Handling**: Improved conflict resolution when notes exist in both systems\r\n\r\n**Breaking Changes**\r\n- Frontmatter keys are now normalized (hyphenated keys automatically repaired)\r\n- Some internal APIs refactored for better type safety\r\n\r\n## Statistics\r\n\r\n- **71 files changed**: 9,488 insertions(+), 3,488 deletions(-)\r\n- Major refactoring of sync engine and UI components\r\n- Comprehensive test coverage added for new features\r\n\r\n## Full Changelog\r\n\r\n- [1.1.1...1.1.2](https://github.com/lc0rp/KeepSidian/compare/1.1.1...1.1.2)",
