      "author": "github-actions[bot]",
      "description": "## What's Changed\r\n\r\n### 🌟 New & Notable\r\n\r\n- **Auto-sync** with a configurable interval to pull in your latest Google Keep notes in the background.\r\n- **Status bar notifications** show real-time sync progress.\r\n- **A progress modal** shows sync details upon clicking the status bar notifications.\r\n- **Activity logs** provide per-run log entries on a daily rotation.\r\n\r\n**Features**\r\n- Auto and manual syncs share the new progress UI and write `_KeepSidianLogs/` entries with start/end summaries and per-note updates.\r\n- Attachment downloads sanitise Keep-provided filenames, resolve relative URLs against your server, and reuse identical media instead of redownloading.\r\n- Duplicate detection merges note bodies safely so you can keep editing in Obsidian without losing server updates.\r\n\r\n**Enhancements**\r\n- Attachments honour Google Keep blob names, resolve relative URLs, and skip identical downloads to save vault space.\r\n- Duplicate handling merges note bodies without touching frontmatter, only creating conflict copies when content truly differs.\r\n- Syncs verify save folders and log files exist before running, surfacing clear notices when setup fails.\r\n- Responses from the Keep server are now validated with Zod and translated into typed network/parse/IO errors for clearer troubleshooting.\r\n\r\n**Fixes**\r\n- Note merging now strips frontmatter before comparison, preventing duplicated metadata blocks.\r\n- Sync UI no longer shows stale failure notices after a successful retry and avoids “missing note” pagination errors.\r\n- Attachment filenames are sanitised and relative blob URLs resolve correctly, preventing failed downloads.\r\n\r\n**Full Changelog**\r\n- <https://github.com/lc0rp/KeepSidian/compare/1.0.15...1.1.1>\r\n",
